I got a TransportError and the error-handler bugs out when trying to tell me what it is.

The TransportError.info is::

```.py
{
    u'status': 400, 
    u'error': u'MapperParsingException[No handler for type [attachment] declared on field [file]]'
}
```

As of commit ade841a6805abc4d4422bd49f2a639fee9b81e69, `TransportError.__str__` does

        try:
            if self.info:
                cause = ', %r' % self.info['error']['root_cause'][0]['reason']
        except LookupError:
            pass

The LookupError would catch either a KeyError or an IndexError. However, `self.info['error']` is a string here, and trying to take the `['root_cause']` of a string results in a TypeError, because "string indices must be integers, not str."

(I think this is why #332 has an "unprintable TransportError")

